# Installation

## Download the package
```
wget https://repo.protonvpn.com/debian/dists/stable/main/binary-all/protonvpn-stable-release_1.0.8_all.deb
```

## Install the Proton VPN Repository containing the app
```
sudo dpkg -i ./protonvpn-stable-release_1.0.8_all.deb && sudo apt update
```

## Install the App
```
sudo apt install proton-vpn-gnome-desktop
```

## (Optional) Enable desktop support tray icons if desired
```
sudo apt install libayatana-appindicator3-1 gir1.2-ayatanaappindicator3-0.1 gnome-shell-extension-appindicator
```
Then restart ProtonVPN if running

## Download CLI
```
sudo apt install proton-vpn-cli
```

# Commands 

## Sign in
```
protonvpn signin [username]
```

## Connect to the fastest VPN server available
```
protonvpn connect
```

## Connect to a specific country
```
protonvpn connect --country [Country]
```

### Examples: (Not Case Sensitive)
```
protonvpn connect --country US
protonvpn connect --country "United States"
protonvpn connect --city [City]
protonvpn connect --city miami
protonvpn connect --city "New York"
protonvpn connect [server name]
protonvpn connect CH#242
```
### List of servers: 
https://protonvpn.com/vpn-servers

## Disconnect
```
protonvpn disconnect
```

## Sign out
```
protonvpn signout
```
